    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-21T23:15:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-21T23:15:00-05:00" n="277"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d277">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9567: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Commander in Chief of the United States Asiatic Fleet</hi>
                        (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Yarnell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the Chief of Naval Operations</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="68" xml:id="d277fn68">Copy transmitted to the Department by
                        the Navy Department.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-22T12:15:00+08:00"
                            >August 22, 1937—12:15 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 22—6 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>0022. Joint letter signed by American, British and French Admirals<note n="69"
                        xml:id="d277fn69">
                        <ref target="frus1931-41v01#pg_487">
                            <hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, Japan, 1931–1941, vol. <hi
                                rend="smallcaps">i</hi>, p. 487</ref>.</note> has been sent to
                    Admiral Hasegawa protesting against presence of a Japanese destroyer about 300
                    yards down stream from <hi rend="italic">Augusta</hi> and requesting that all
                    Japanese vessels be kept below Hongkew Creek. Substance of reply will be
                    communicated when received.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
